Package org.opennars.language

Class Interval

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opennars.language.Term
      • org.opennars.language.Interval
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<AbstractTerm>, AbstractTerm
    public class Interval
extends Term
    This stores the magnitude of a time difference, which is the logarithm of the time difference in base D=duration ( @see Param.java ). The actual printed value is +1 more than the stored magnitude, so for example, it will have name() "+1" if magnitude=0, and "+2" if magnitude=1.
    Author:
    Pei Wang, Patrick Hammer
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
